8\",\"source\":\"ProjectManager\",\"models_usage\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"created_at\":\"2026-05-05T15:41:33.249397Z\",\"content\":\"It seems that I'm unable to create directories in the project board due to access restrictions. However, I can still document the issue and create focused tickets based on the problem statement provided.\\n\\n### Triage Summary\\n\\n1. **Root Problem:** The `separability_matrix` function does not compute correct separability for nested CompoundModels. A specific example is provided where the expected diagonal output is not achieved.\\n\\n2. **Reproduced Failures:** Tests that are failing include:\\n   - `astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py::test_separable[compound_model6-result6]`\\n   - `astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py::test_separable[compound_model9-result9]`\\n\\n3. **Passes:** Several tests pass which indicates that the function works correctly for non-nested models and other combinations.\\n\\n### Actionable Tickets\\nI will create tickets for the following tasks:\\n\\n- **[Ticket 1] Investigation**: Review the current logic of the `separability_matrix` function to understand how it handles nested models.\\n\\n- **[Ticket 2] Implementation**: Apply fixes to the implementation of the `separability_matrix` function to ensure correct behavior with nested CompoundModels.\\n\\n- **[Ticket 3] Testing**: Develop new tests or modify existing tests to cover the scenarios with previously failed tests for nested CompoundModels.\\n\\n- **[Ticket 4] Review**: Peer review of the implementation changes.\\n\\nI will proceed to create the first ticket regarding the investigation now.\",\"type\":\"ThoughtEvent\"},{\"id\":\"07203a64-4eb7-45b1-ad1d-210e17eaa735\",\"source\":\"ProjectManager\",\"models_usage\":{\"prompt_tokens\":3207,\"completion_tokens\":466},\"metadata\":{},\"created_at\":\"2026-05-05T15:41:33.250964Z\",\"content\":[{\"id\":\"call_UjoeWQDs1xSg2FcKHxPrvUaZ\",\"arguments\":\"{\\\"path\\\":\\\"investigation/separability_matrix_investigation.md\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"## Investigation Ticket for `separability_matrix`\\\\n\\\\n### Overview\\\\n\\\\nThe goal of this investigation is to understand why the `separability_matrix` function does not compute separable states correctly for nested CompoundModels. This will involve reviewing the existing implementation and identifying any logical flaws in handling nesting.\\\\n\\\\n### Steps to Investigate:\\\\n1. Review the implementation of the `separability_matrix` function in the relevant source file (likely `separable.py`).\\\\n2. Identify sections of the code where the logic for separation may incorrectly assume independence between nested models.\\\\n3. Document findings and propose adjustments to the logic as necessary.\\\"}\",\"name\":\"board_write_file\"}],\"type\":\"ToolCallRequestEvent\"},{\"id\":\"261a9feb-d51b-45fd-a0f4-ae3c7a403885\",\"source\":\"ProjectManager\",\"models_usage\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"created_at\":\"2026-05-05T15:41:33.263204Z\",\"content\":[{\"content\":\"Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/project_board/investigation/separability_matrix_investigation.md not in /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-evaluate-pipeline/runs/example-study/mas_centralize/astropy__astropy-12907/repeat_1/project_board\",\"name\":\"board_write_file\",\"call_id\":\"call_UjoeWQDs1xSg2FcKHxPrvUaZ\",\"is_error\":false}],\"type\":\"ToolCallExecutionEvent\"}]},\"name\":\"ProjectManager\"}", "sender": "ProjectManager_adfdccfc-314c-4235-b37b-9e223857280a/adfdccfc-314c-4235-b37b-9e223857280a", "receiver": null, "kind": "MessageKind.PUBLISH", "delivery_stage": "DeliveryStage.DELIVER", "type": "Message"}
